OL,3,CThe man whose 'gift' for helping
OL,4,Cothers cost him his life
OL,6,FMs Williams worked with Mr Marriott, a
OL,7,Ffather-of-two, in her capacity as
OL,8,Fchief executive of the charity Jubilee
OL,9,FPlus. Mr Marriott, who was 46, was a
OL,10,Fvolunteer.
OL,12,FHe also worked at a foodbank in
OL,13,FSheffield.
OL,15,F"When I heard that he went to stop to
OL,16,Fhelp someone in the road, it was
OL,17,Fentirely in keeping with his
OL,18,Fcharacter," Ms Williams said. "It's
OL,19,Fexactly what I would expect Chris to
OL,20,Fdo in that situation - to go and help
OL,21,Fsomeone."
